<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Proposal: Make it possible to set different cache debug_headers or disable them based on regexps.</p>

<p>Also it would be cool if you can add an http header and not only</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code> 
cause this breaks json responses for example.


</code></pre>

<p>$frontendOptions = array(
   'lifetime' =&gt; 10,
   'debug_header' =&gt; true,
   'regexps' =&gt; array(
       '^/json/$' =&gt; array('debug_header' =&gt; false), // im an json response no debug header please
       '^/json2/$' =&gt; array('debug_header_http' =&gt; 'x-header-zendcache'), // im an json response and thus i got a real http debug header
   )
);
```</p>

<p>Would be nice to have this possibility for phpunit / selenium etc.</p>

